	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=119042><span id=Scholar>KhallimBloodhelm</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>24 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.33]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I beleive he did mean &quot;if they have TBags&quot;, Troodon.&nbsp;&nbsp;Its a common practice you would probably only understand if you had been on a Naggy/Vox/Severilous/Talendor/Trak raid.  Similar thing happens for Cloak of Flames, the haste item.  The people who have a lesser item of the same type (i.e. Haste or weight reducing item, etc) roll on this new and better item.  Then they give their less efective items (Such as a Tbag for the Treasure Hunters Satchel, or an FBSS or Sash of Dragonborn for the CoF) to the raid leader, and then the rest of the raid roles on those items.  <br><br>Its kinda like, ok, I have this better item now, so I don't need this, but since you all helped me get the better item, you can roll on and have my old item.  (Usually what happens is everyone rolls on the nice item, and IF someone with another less good item gets the Bad or Cloak, then they donate, voluntarily, their old item to be rolled on.)<br><br>Hope that just clears things up a bit.<br><br>Khallim Bloodhelm<br>Dwarven Merc of the 51st Blade<br>~Some men are alive simply because its against the law to kill them~</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
